This is a placeholder.

We are using very old versions of the Chromium build system, and Chromium build
from that era wants a libc++-static library for Mac.  This has since been
removed from Chromium, because it is not necessary in newer macOS SDKs.  Even
though we target a new enough version of macOS not to need the libc++-static
hack, the build system still tells the compiler to expect this folder to exist.
The contents are not actually needed, though.
